  <scopecontent id="aspace_cd4cc8bb3c18c141e2f70d6f71bbad1d">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Collection consists of correspondence between 19th and early 20th century French composers, librettists and musicians (including Fromental Halévy, Jean-François Le Sueur, Jules Massenet, Eugène Scribe, Florent Schmitt, and others). Many of the letters are addressed to musicologist Georges Servières (1858 - 1937). Also includes music manuscripts, programs, engravings, and clippings.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_081bf526ad7f1ad9b3494331c3dc5bc1">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Ben Grauer collection of French music correspondence, #8434. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
